#Approach:

Approach:
Ye code sliding window + hashing use karta hai longest substring without repeating characters ke liye.

1. Do pointers use hue hain:
   - l = window ka left
   - r = window ka right
2. hash array me har character ka last seen index store hota hai.
3. Jab current character repeat milta hai aur uska last index current window ke andar hai,
   to left pointer ko uske next position par shift kar dete hain.
4. Isse window me duplicate character nahi rehta.
5. Har step par current window length = r - l + 1 nikaal kar maxLen update karte hain.
6. Fir current character ka latest index hash me update kar dete hain.

Main idea:
Window ko continuously expand karte hain,
aur jaise hi duplicate aaye, left ko jump kara dete hain
taaki substring unique bani rahe.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)   // fixed hash array

#Code:

class Solution {
    public int lengthOfLongestSubstring(String s) {
        int[] hash = new int[256];
        Arrays.fill(hash, -1);
        int n = s.length();

        int maxLen = 0;
        int l = 0;
        int r = 0;

        while(r < n){
            if(hash[s.charAt(r)] != -1){
                if(hash[s.charAt(r)] >= l){
                    l = hash[s.charAt(r)] + 1;
                }
            }
            maxLen = Math.max(maxLen, r-l+1);
            hash[s.charAt(r)] = r;
            r++;
        }
        return maxLen;
    }
}
